http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Sarada-Devi-hailed-as-%E2%80%98Holy-Mother%E2%80%99-on-164th-birthday-anniversary/article13976672.ece

TIRUPATI: The New Year began on an auspicious note for the followers of the Ramakrishna Vivekananda School of Thought, with the 164th birth anniversary of Holy Mother Sri Sarada Devi falling on this day.In his address to the devotees on the occasion, Swami Anupamananda, Secretary of the Ramakrishna Mission’s Tirupati ashrama, hailed Sarada Devi as a symbol of purity, divinity, simplicity and holiness, and explained the manner she is revered among the Ramakrishna order as ‘Sangha Janani’. He also eulogised her for leading the mission after Sri Ramakrishna for three decades.Food, sarees and blankets were distributed to the poor on the occasion, after the conduct of special ‘Mangalarati’, ‘Homam’ and ‘Sahasranama Stotram’. In the evening, Sri Padmavathi Mahila Viswa Vidyalayam V-C V. Durga Bhavani took part as the chief guest and addressed the devotees on the ideals of Sarada Devi.The mission announced to observe the birthday of Swami Vivekananda on Jan 12 as ‘National Youth Day’ in a grand manner at the Ashrama premises. Prizes to the winners of the elocution, essay writing and drawing competitions conducted earlier will be distributed on the occasion.Kakinada Staff Reporter adds: Sri Ramakrishna Seva Samithi on Friday celebrated the birth anniversary of Sri Sarada devi. Samithi president C. Suryanarayana, retired lecturer V. Ramakrishna recalled the services rendered by Ramakrishna Paramahamsa and Sarada Mata to the mankind on the occasion.